==Translingual==

===Symbol===
'''Α'''
# The [[upper case]] letter [[alpha]], the first letter of the modern [[w:Greek alphabet|Greek alphabet]].

'''Α''''
# The number one in [[w:Greek numerals|Greek numerals]].

''',Α'''
# The number 1000 in Greek numerals.

===Pronunciation===
* In modern Greek it represents [[w:Open front unrounded vowel|[a]]], similar to the '''a''' in ''hat''.

===Etymology===
* Derived from the Phoenician letter [[w:Aleph (letter)|Aleph]] [[Image:phoenician_aleph.png|20px|Aleph]].

